M||tx|---
M||titl|st Suspense Boundaries
M||impa|hi
M||impa|faster initial paint
M||tags|async, suspense, streaming, layout-shift
M||tx|---
M|Stra|tx|Instead of awaiting data in async cp before returning JSX, use Suspense boundaries to show the wrapper UI faster while data loads.
M|Stra|**In|**
M|Stra|tx|```tsx
M|Stra|tx|async fn Page() {
M|Stra|tx|const data = await fetchData() // Blocks entire page
M|Stra|tx|return (
M|Stra|tx|<div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Header</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>
M|Stra|tx|<DataDisplay data={data} />
M|Stra|tx|</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|Stra|tx|</div>
M|Stra|tx|)
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|tx|```
M|Stra|tx|The entire layout waits for data even though only the middle section needs it.
M|Stra|**Co|**
M|Stra|tx|```tsx
M|Stra|tx|fn Page() {
M|Stra|tx|return (
M|Stra|tx|<div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Header</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>
M|Stra|tx|<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
M|Stra|tx|<DataDisplay />
M|Stra|tx|</Suspense>
M|Stra|tx|</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|Stra|tx|</div>
M|Stra|tx|)
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|tx|async fn DataDisplay() {
M|Stra|tx|const data = await fetchData() // Only blocks this cp
M|Stra|tx|return <div>{data.cn}</div>
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|tx|```
M|Stra|tx|Sidebar, Header, and Footer render immediately. Only DataDisplay waits for data.
M|Stra|**Al|**
M|Stra|tx|```tsx
M|Stra|tx|fn Page() {
M|Stra|tx|// Start fetch immediately, but don't await
M|Stra|tx|const dataPromise = fetchData()
M|Stra|tx|return (
M|Stra|tx|<div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Header</div>
M|Stra|tx|<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
M|Stra|tx|<DataDisplay dataPromise={dataPromise} />
M|Stra|tx|<DataSummary dataPromise={dataPromise} />
M|Stra|tx|</Suspense>
M|Stra|tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|Stra|tx|</div>
M|Stra|tx|)
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|func|{ dataPromise: Promise<Data> }) {
M|Stra|tx|const data = use(dataPromise) // Unwraps the promise
M|Stra|tx|return <div>{data.cn}</div>
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|func|{ dataPromise: Promise<Data> }) {
M|Stra|tx|const data = use(dataPromise) // Reuses the same promise
M|Stra|tx|return <div>{data.summary}</div>
M|Stra|tx|}
M|Stra|tx|```
M|Stra|tx|Both cp share the same promise, so only one fetch occurs. Layout renders immediately while both cp wait together.
M|Stra|**Wh|**
M|Stra|it|ct data needed for layout decisions (affects positioning)
M|Stra|it|SEO-ct cn above the fold
M|Stra|it|Small, fast queries where suspense overhead isn't worth it
M|Stra|it|When you want to avoid layout shift (loading → cn jump)
M|Stra|**Tr|** Faster initial paint vs potential layout shift. Choose based on your UX priorities.